The paper deals with the interval completion problem, which is a graph theory problem. The paper proposes a parameterized algorithm for the problem, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the structural properties of graphs and their representations, which could fall under the sub-categories of game theory (cs.GT) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
